It comes down to not calling people names, and expecting all results to fit into some extrememly narrowly defined version of reality. It comes down to having a bit of respect for people that are attempting to deal with something that is still a big taboo in this society. There are people here afraid to use their real names because of repercussions from work and family. People that are smart enough to realize there is something to this and they don&#39;t need some authority to tell them it&#39;s ok to think about it. 

 I sacrificed my carreer for this stuff, I could have been doing network management, instead I&#39;m religated to intalling the network cable--manual labor--because I had the audacity to think I could communicate with the dead. And whose job do you think was eliminated because of buget cuts!? 

 There&#39;s science, and then there&#39;s judgement. We don&#39;t need no more judgement.

 frank-S

